Currently, when someone shares a page with you or sends a link to a page that you don't have access to, you just get a not found page.

Instead should show you a 'request access' button which you can hit and the page owner gets an email saying you want to view the page and links to somewhere to quickly add access.

h4. Symptoms

When piwik's tracking html/javascript code is embedded into a page in Confluence, clicking edit does not work as expected. At first it displays a blank page, and then after a few more seconds it redirects to a "Page Not Found".

h4. Steps to Reproduce

# Confluence Admin > Custom HTML
# Enter the following code in the "at the end of the BODY" section:
{code:html}<!-- Piwik --> 
<script type="text/javascript">
var pkBaseURL = (("https:" == document.location.protocol) ? "https://multisitenexus.com/piwik/" : "http://multisitenexus.com/piwik/");
document.write(unescape("%3Cscript src='" + pkBaseURL + "piwik.js' type='text/javascript'%3E%3C/script%3E"));
</script><script type="text/javascript">
try {
var piwikTracker = Piwik.getTracker(pkBaseURL + "piwik.php", 1);
piwikTracker.trackPageView();
piwikTracker.enableLinkTracking();
} catch( err ) {}
</script><noscript><p><img src="http://multisitenexus.com/piwik/piwik.php?idsite=1" style="border:0" alt="" /></p></noscript>
<!-- End Piwik Tracking Code -->{code}
# Try to edit any page

Custom CSS does not apply to elements in the Admin console of in the page view (neither edit nor display mode)

I have this custom CSS defined:
{code}
.atlwdg-trigger {  
background:white !important;  
border-color:grey !important;  
}  
{code}

This CSS displays correctly in other areas of Confluence, eg the Dashboard, but it lost when in the Admin console and in Page view.

h3. Steps to reproduce
# Create a JIRA Issue Collector
# Add it to Confluence
# Add the above CSS to change the appearance of the connector
# View to Dashboard
#- Observe that the collector changes colour
# View the Admin Console
#- Observe that the collector does not have the custom CSS applied
# View a page
#- Observe that the collector does not have the custom CSS applied

